public class Frame
extends Box<Widget>

A base class for frame widgets.

A frame widget is a Box that normally has two basic Boxes as its children. Its first child is for the title of the frame; its second child is for the content of the frame.

The Box's methods for Frame have been overridden and redirected to its content box.

Author:
J.J.Liu (Jianjun Liu) at http://www.jscripter.org

public Frame()

Constructs a default frame widget.

This constructor invokes Frame(Component) with a new component created by calling Component.div() as argument.

Frame

protected Frame(Component e)

Typically constructs a frame widget.

This constructor invokes its super constructor and creates its title box with a CSS sub selector "tbox" expended and content box with a CSS sub selector "tbox" expended.

children

public ArrayLike<Widget> children()

Gets an array of child widgets of frame's content.

This overriding method redirects its invocation to that of the same method of the content box.

Box.children() has to be used to get the real children of this box, but normally this situation is not expected.

add
